\n- When a step combines a condition with another action (e.g., \u0060if X, call GoalName\u0060 or \u0060if X, set %y% = 1\u0060), produce multiple actions in the same step: \u0060condition.if\u0060 first, then the conditional action(s). The orchestrator handles running or skipping them.\n","user":"TestRunReportsAssertionFailure\n/ Integration: fixture test that deliberately fails an assertion (assert %x%\nequals \u0027wrong\u0027 when %x%=\u0027right\u0027). Expected TestStatus.Fail with the\nAssertionError carrying Expected, Actual, and Variables snapshot (the\nfull diagnostic surface from Batch 5).\n- write out \u0027TODO: not implemented\u0027  \u003C= null\n\n","response":{"description":"Maps the single step \u0027write out ...\u0027 to an output.write action. The provided text indicates a failing assertion test, but no explicit assertion step or variables are specified in the goal step list; only the write-out step is actionable here.","errors":[],"warnings":[],"steps":[{"index":0,"guidance":"The step says to write out a message. Use output.write with the literal user-facing text. No \u0027write to %var%\u0027 is present, so no variable.set is required.","actions":[{"module":"output","action":"write","parameters":[{"name":"Data","value":"TODO: not implemented","type":"tstring"},{"name":"Channels","value":"this","type":"string"}]}],"level":"high","confidence":95}]}},"detailPasses":[]}
