n- **medium** (40-79%) \u2014 module/action identified, parameters uncertain\n- **low** (0-39%) \u2014 best guess\n\n## Step Grouping\n\nWhen steps are logically related and understanding one helps build the others, assign them the same \u0060group\u0060 name. If any step in a group needs the detail pass (medium/low), ALL steps in the group are sent together so the LLM sees the full flow.\n\nGroup when:\n- Steps form a multi-step pattern (e.g., read file \u2192 process \u2192 write result)\n- A condition step and its indented sub-steps are related\n- Steps share variables or data flow between them\n- Error handling spans multiple steps\n\nDo NOT group unrelated steps. Steps without a group are processed individually. Use short descriptive names: \u0022file-processing\u0022, \u0022auth-flow\u0022, \u0022data-transform\u0022, etc.\n\n## Example\n\nGoal:\n\u0060\u0060\u0060plang\nStart\n- call goal Greet name=\u0022world\u0022\n- read file \u0027config.json\u0027, write to %config%\n    cache for 5 minutes\n- if %config.debug% is true\n    - write out \u0022debug mode\u0022\n- foreach %config.items%, call ProcessItem item=%item%\n- call Save, on error retry 2 times, then call HandleError\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nResponse:\n\u0060\u0060\u0060json\n{\n  \u0022description\u0022: \u0022Calls Greet, reads cached config, conditional debug output, iterates items, saves with retry.\u0022,\n  \u0022steps\u0022: [\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 0,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022goal.call to Greet with name parameter\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022goal\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022call\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Greet\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022name\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022world\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 1,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022file.read with cache.wrap modifier (5 min = 300000ms), then variable.set to capture %config%. The cache.wrap modifier wraps only the file.read, not the variable.set.\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [\n        {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022file\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022read\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Path\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022config.json\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022path\u0022}]},\n        {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022cache\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022wrap\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022DurationMs\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: 300000, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022long\u0022}]},\n        {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022variable\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022set\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Name\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%config%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Value\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%__data__%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022object\u0022}]}\n      ],\n      \u0022group\u0022: \u0022config-check\u0022,\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 2,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022condition checking config.debug, sub-step below handles true case\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022condition\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022if\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Left\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%config.debug%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022bool\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Operator\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022==\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Right\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: true, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022bool\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022group\u0022: \u0022config-check\u0022,\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 90\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 3,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022output.write indented under condition \u2014 only runs if config.debug is true\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022output\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022write\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Data\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022debug mode\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022group\u0022: \u0022config-check\u0022,\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 98\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 4,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022loop.foreach iterates collection, goal.call is the loop body \u2014 two separate actions, orchestrator runs goal.call per item\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022loop\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022foreach\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Collection\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%config.items%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022object\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022ItemName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022item\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}, {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022goal\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022call\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022ProcessItem\u0022}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 5,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022goal.call to Save with error.handle modifier for retry \u002B error goal. The modifier wraps the goal.call.\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [\n        {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022goal\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022call\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Save\u0022}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]},\n        {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022error\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022handle\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022RetryCount\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: 2, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022int\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Order\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022RetryFirst\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Goal\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022HandleError\u0022}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]}\n      ],\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n## Multi-Action Patterns (CRITICAL)\n\nThese patterns ALWAYS produce multiple actions in one step. Missing the second action is a build-breaking bug.\n\n**\u0022write to \\%var\\%\u0022** \u2192 TWO actions: the main action PLUS \u0060variable.set\u0060\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\nstep: \u0022render template \u0027foo.md\u0027, write to %result%\u0022\nactions: [\n  {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022ui\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022render\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [...]},\n  {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022variable\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022set\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Name\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%result%\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Value\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%__data__%\u0022}]}\n]\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\nThe engine stores each action\u0027s result as \\%__data__\\%. The variable.set reads it. This applies to EVERY step containing \u0022write to \\%var\\%\u0022 \u2014 file.read, builder.actions, builder.types, ui.render, llm.query, list.group, etc. If the step text contains \u0022write to\u0022, you MUST produce a variable.set action. No exceptions.\n\n**\u0022foreach \\%list\\%, call GoalName\u0022** \u2192 TWO actions: \u0060loop.foreach\u0060 PLUS \u0060goal.call\u0060\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\nstep: \u0022foreach %items%, call ProcessItem item=%item%\u0022\nactions: [\n  {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022loop\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022foreach\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Collection\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%items%\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022ItemName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022item\u0022}]},\n  {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022goal\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022call\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022ProcessItem\u0022}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]}\n]\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\nThe foreach iterates, the goal.call runs per item. Both actions are required.\n\n**\u0022llm.query system=..., user=...\u0022** \u2192 Messages is \u0060list\u003Cllmmessage\u003E\u0060, map shorthand to message objects\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\nstep: \u0022llm.query system=%prompt%, user=%input%, schema={result: string}, write to %answer%\u0022\nactions: [\n  {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022llm\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022query\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [\n    {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Messages\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: [{\u0022Role\u0022: \u0022system\u0022, \u0022Content\u0022: \u0022%prompt%\u0022}, {\u0022Role\u0022: \u0022user\u0022, \u0022Content\u0022: \u0022%input%\u0022}], \u0022type\u0022: \u0022list\u003Cllmmessage\u003E\u0022},\n    {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Schema\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022{\\\u0022result\\\u0022:\\\u0022string\\\u0022}\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}\n  ]},\n  {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022variable\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022set\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Name\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%answer%\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Value\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%__data__%\u0022}]}\n]\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\u0060system=\u0060 becomes \u0060{\u0022Role\u0022: \u0022system\u0022, \u0022Content\u0022: \u0022...\u0022}\u0060, \u0060user=\u0060 becomes \u0060{\u0022Role\u0022: \u0022user\u0022, \u0022Content\u0022: \u0022...\u0022}\u0060. Always build the Messages list from these. The \u0060schema=\u0060 shorthand maps to the \u0060Schema\u0060 string parameter.\n\n## Rules\n\n- Step count in response MUST match step count in goal. Comments (/) are NOT steps. \u0060on error\u0060 is part of its step, not separate.\n- Comments are documentation only \u2014 never influence action mapping.\n- Variables use \\%name\\% syntax \u2014 preserve literally.\n- NEVER use \u0060\u0022return\u0022\u0060 on actions. There is no return property. Variable assignment is always an explicit \u0060variable.set\u0060 action.\n- For \u0060goal.call\u0060: simple = \u0060{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022}\u0060, with params = \u0060{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022key\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022val\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}\u0060.\n- Omit nullable parameters (types ending ?) when not applicable.\n- \\%variable\\% references resolve at runtime. Never pre-evaluate.\n- Literal JSON types: \u0060true\u0060/\u0060false\u0060 (boolean), numbers unquoted, strings quoted. \u0060type\u0060 field must match.\n- When \u0060set \\%var\\% = {key: value, ...}\u0060 contains an inline object (curly braces), the Value parameter must use \u0060\u0022type\u0022: \u0022json\u0022\u0060 and the value must be a **JSON object** (not a string containing JSON). Example: \u0060{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Value\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022id\u0022: \u0022\\%x\\%\u0022, \u0022items\u0022: []}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022json\u0022}\u0060.\n- \u0060missingVariable\u0060 is ALWAYS a warning \u2014 variables can be set by called goals.\n- NEVER alter literal values. You are a compiler, not an editor.\n- Action modifiers \u2014 any step text expressing cross-cutting behavior around an action (error handling, caching, deadlines) MUST produce a modifier action right after the action it applies to. Modifier actions today: \u0060error.handle\u0060 (on-error / retry / ignore / error-goal), \u0060cache.wrap\u0060 (cache for X), \u0060timeout.after\u0060 (deadline). The builder groups these onto the preceding executable action. Missing a modifier when the step text implies one is a build-breaking bug.\n- Actions within a step execute in order. Each action\u0027s result is available as \\%__data__\\% to the next action.\n- When a step combines a condition with another action (e.g., \u0060if X, call GoalName\u0060 or \u0060if X, set %y% = 1\u0060), produce multiple actions in the same step: \u0060condition.if\u0060 first, then the conditional action(s). The orchestrator handles running or skipping them.\n","user":"Gamma\n- write out \u0027gamma fixture\u0027  \u003C= null\n\n","response":{"description":"Writes the text \u0027gamma fixture\u0027 to output.","errors":[],"warnings":[],"steps":[{"index":0,"guidance":"The step \u0027write out ...\u0027 maps to output.write. The \u0027\u003C= null\u0027 indicates no additional assignment/variable output; no variable.set action is needed.","actions":[{"module":"output","action":"write","parameters":[{"name":"Data","value":"gamma fixture","type":"tstring"},{"name":"Channels","value":"this","type":"string"}]}],"level":"high","confidence":95}]}},"detailPasses":[]}
