r when the step text implies one is a build-breaking bug.\n- Actions within a step execute in order. Each action\u0027s result is available as \\%__data__\\% to the next action.\n- When a step combines a condition with another action (e.g., \u0060if X, call GoalName\u0060 or \u0060if X, set %y% = 1\u0060), produce multiple actions in the same step: \u0060condition.if\u0060 first, then the conditional action(s). The orchestrator handles running or skipping them.\n","user":"Beta\n- write out \u0027beta fixture\u0027  \u003C= null\n\n","response":{"description":"Writes the text \u0027beta fixture\u0027 to output.","errors":[],"warnings":[],"steps":[{"index":0,"guidance":"The step \u0027write out ...\u0027 maps to output.write. The \u0027\u003C= null\u0027 appears to be a nullability annotation and does not change the required engine action.","actions":[{"module":"output","action":"write","parameters":[{"name":"Data","value":"beta fixture","type":"tstring"},{"name":"Channels","value":"this","type":"string"}]}],"level":"high","confidence":90}]}},"detailPasses":[]}
