+{"id":"639123149400903483_TestReportIncludesCoverageTables","goal":"TestReportIncludesCoverageTables","timestamp":"2026-04-20T20:49:00.0917735+00:00","pass1":{"system":"# Goal Builder\n\nYou are the PLang compiler. Map each step in a goal to engine actions.\n\n## How the Engine Works\n\nThe engine has **modules** (namespaces) with **action classes**. Each action class has properties and a \u0060Run()\u0060 method.\n\nYour job: for each step, produce \u0060{module, action, parameters}\u0060 where:\n- \u0060module\u0060 = namespace (output, file, goal, condition, variable, etc.)\n- \u0060action\u0060 = class name (write, read, call, if, set, etc.)\n- \u0060parameters\u0060 = list of \u0060{name, value, type}\u0060 matching the class properties\n\nThe engine does: find class \u2192 set properties \u2192 call Run().\n\n## Available Actions\n\nFormat: \u0060- module.action ParamName([type] value)\u0060 where ? = optional, = val is default, %var% = variable reference\nTypes: tstring = translatable string \u2014 use for any user-facing text (output, messages, labels). When a variable resolves to a string at runtime, it becomes tstring automatically.\n\nExample: \u0060- goal.call GoalName([goal.call] {\u0022name\u0022:\u0022Greet\u0022,\u0022parameters\u0022:[{\u0022name\u0022:\u0022x\u0022,\u0022value\u0022:1}]})\u0060 becomes:\n\u0060\u0060\u0060json\n{\u0022module\u0022:\u0022goal\u0022,\u0022action\u0022:\u0022call\u0022,\u0022parameters\u0022:[{\u0022name\u0022:\u0022GoalName\u0022,\u0022value\u0022:{\u0022name\u0022:\u0022Greet\u0022,\u0022parameters\u0022:[{\u0022name\u0022:\u0022x\u0022,\u0022value\u0022:1}]},\u0022type\u0022:\u0022goal.call\u0022}]}\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nActions:\n\n- module.remove [no-cache] Name([string])\n- module.add [no-cache] Path([string]), Namespace([string?])\n\n- goal.return [no-cache] Data([object?]), Depth([int = 1])\n- goal.call GoalName([goal.call]), Actor([this?(user|service|system)])\n\n- variable.get Name([%var% string])\n- varia