r when the step text implies one is a build-breaking bug.\n- Actions within a step execute in order. Each action\u0027s result is available as \\%__data__\\% to the next action.\n- When a step combines a condition with another action (e.g., \u0060if X, call GoalName\u0060 or \u0060if X, set %y% = 1\u0060), produce multiple actions in the same step: \u0060condition.if\u0060 first, then the conditional action(s). The orchestrator handles running or skipping them.\n","user":"Slow\n- timer.sleep 5000 milliseconds  \u003C= null\n- write out \u0027should not reach here\u0027  \u003C= null\n\n","response":{"description":"Sleep for 5000ms, then attempt to write output that should not be reached (no explicit control-flow provided).","errors":[],"warnings":[],"steps":[{"index":0,"guidance":"Map \u0027timer.sleep 5000 milliseconds\u0027 to timer.sleep with Ms=5000. The \u0027\u003C= null\u0027 is not a recognized parameter in the engine actions, so it is ignored.","actions":[{"module":"timer","action":"sleep","parameters":[{"name":"Ms","value":5000,"type":"int"}]}],"level":"high","confidence":95},{"index":1,"guidance":"Map \u0027write out ...\u0027 to output.write. The \u0027\u003C= null\u0027 is not a recognized parameter, so it is ignored.","actions":[{"module":"output","action":"write","parameters":[{"name":"Data","value":"should not reach here","type":"tstring"}]}],"level":"high","confidence":90}]}},"detailPasses":[]}
