+/ Companion to TestReportMasksSensitiveVariables — same fixture, but with
+/ format='junit' so the committed junit.xml snapshot can be eyeballed.
+/ Proves the JUnit XML path also masks [Sensitive] PrivateKey — BuildJUnit
+/ emits run.Error?.Message directly, so AssertionError.Message itself must
+/ be sanitised (not just the structured JSON envelope).
+- test.discover tests in '_fixtures_sensitive', pattern='*.fixture.goal', recursive, write to %tests%
+- test.run tests %tests%, write to %results%
+- test.report results %results%, format='junit', write to %report%
+- assert %report.summaryFail% equals 1
+- assert %report.content% contains '<testsuites'
+- assert %report.content% contains 'privateKey'
+- assert %report.content% contains '******'
+- assert %report.content% contains 'publicKey'
+- file.save path='snapshots/junit_sensitive_masked.xml', content=%report.content%
